      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum FEA with nonlinear contact is appropriate for the metallic construct; model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis on friction coefficient and contact stiffness.",
      "rationale": "Implicit nonlinear FEA with Hertzian contact formulation captures the dominant load-transfer mechanism at the screw-rod interface. Sensitivity studies on friction coefficient (0.1–0.3) showed < 4% variation in yield force, consistent with the observed inter-laboratory experimental scatter."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
