    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA ensemble demonstrates adequate predictive accuracy for all three QoIs within the pre-established acceptance bounds. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions) is acknowledged and accepted given the standardized nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol. One factor (Relevance of validation activities to COU) was not assessed in this submission cycle and is noted as beyond scope pending further clinical context review. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the Medium assurance level decision for this Class II device.",
